  <problem>

<p>A binary system consists of stars of masses \(m\) and \(2m\), separated by distance \(L\). The stars are revolving in circular orbits around their common center of mass. The centripetal acceleration of the star with the smaller mass is \(a_c\).</p>

<p>What is the centripetal acceleration \(a'_c\) of the other star?</p>

<multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="yes" type="MultipleChoice">
  <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
	<choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="true">\(a'_c = a_c/2\)</choice>
	<choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">\(a'_c = Gm^2 / L^2\)</choice>
	<choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">\(a'_c = Gm^2 / L\)</choice>
	<choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">\(a'_c = Gm / (2L^2)\)</choice>
	<choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">\(a'_c = 2Gm / L^2\)</choice>
	<choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">\(a'_c = 2a_c\)</choice>
  </choicegroup>
</multiplechoiceresponse>

<p>Find the period of revolutions of the stars.</p>

<multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="1r" type="MultipleChoice">
  <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
	<choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="true">\(T=2 \pi \sqrt{2L/(3a_c)}\)</choice>
	<choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">\(T=2 \pi \sqrt{3L/(2a_c)}\)</choice>
	<choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">\(T=2 \pi \sqrt{L/a_c}\)</choice>
	<choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">\(T=2 \pi \sqrt{L/(3a_c)}\)</choice>
	<choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">\(T= \pi \sqrt{2L/(3a_c)}\)</choice>
	<choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">\(T=4 \pi \sqrt{L/(3a_c)}\)</choice>
  </choicegroup>
</multiplechoiceresponse>

  </problem>
</html>
